
                                            Two herdsmen looking for their cattle discovered the bodies in bushes in Coega on Saturday morning.
                                         CAPE TOWN - The bodies of four men who are believed to have been abducted in Port Elizabeth have been found. Two herdsmen looking for their cattle discovered the bodies in bushes in Coega on Saturday morning. It's believed that the deceased were stabbed and strangled. The police's Andre Beetge: "Due to the state of decomposition of the bodies, we strongly suspect that the men are the same persons that were abducted on Thursday morning, just after midnight.  "An unknown amount of persons allegedly abducted four males at gunpoint from the home of one of the males at Makhubela Street in New Brighton and left with them in white Volkswagen Jetta."